ABREVIATIONS

DATA SOURCES

The data sources used in this analysis will be determined empirically by evaluating the study inputs against pre-computed characterization results. This method generates a rough estimate determining which databases have the information necessary to observe both the outcomes and exposures of interest in the required populations. Only databases that pass data diagnostics will be used in the study.

APPENDIX

Module Versions

The OHDSI Strategus modules used in this study are:

Cohorts

Pulmonary Arterial Hypertension

Cohort Entry Events

People may enter the cohort when observing any of the following:

  1. condition occurrence of âPulmonary arterial hypertensionâ for the first time in the personâs history.

Limit cohort entry events to the earliest event per person.

Restrict entry events to with any of the following criteria:

  1. having at least 1 procedure occurrence of âRight Heart Catheterizationâ, starting anytime up to 30 days after cohort entry start date.
  2. having at least 1 procedure occurrence of âEchocardiogramâ, starting anytime up to 30 days after cohort entry start date.

Cohort Exit

The person exits the cohort at the end of continuous observation.

Cohort Eras

Entry events will be combined into cohort eras if they are within 0 days of each other.

Cohort Entry Events

Pulmonary hypertension associated with left heart disease (WHO Group 2)

Cohort Entry Events

People may enter the cohort when observing any of the following:

  1. condition occurrences of âPulmonary Hypertension group 2 and general Pulmonary Hypertensionâ.

Limit cohort entry events to the earliest event per person.

Inclusion Criteria

1. Must have Left heart disease : within last 365 days

Entry events having at least 1 condition occurrence of âLeft Heart Disease (for Pulmonary Hypertension group 2)â, starting between 365 days before and 7 days after cohort entry start date; allow events outside observation period.

2. Must have undegone Echocardiography or RHC: within last 365 days

Entry events having at least 1 procedure occurrence of âEchocardiography & Right Heart Catheterizationâ, starting between 365 days before and 0 days before cohort entry start date; allow events outside observation period.

Cohort Exit

The person exits the cohort at the end of continuous observation.

Cohort Eras

Entry events will be combined into cohort eras if they are within 0 days of each other.

Cohort Entry Events

  1. condition occurrences of âAcute myocardial Infarctionâ.
